---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const structuredData = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "name": "About GenAIPick",
  "description": "Learn about GenAIPick - honest, hands-on AI tool reviews and tutorials.",
  "url": "https://genaipick.com/about/"
});
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about GenAIPick - honest, hands-on AI tool reviews and tutorials for people who actually use AI tools."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <div class="static-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="static-content">
        <h1>About GenAIPick</h1>
        
        <p>Welcome to GenAIPick. I'm a tech enthusiast who's been using AI tools since before they were cool. I've watched the AI space explode over the past few years, and I've tried probably too many of these tools.</p>
        
        <p>Why did I start this site? Because most AI tool reviews are either:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sponsored content disguised as reviews</li>
          <li>Listicles that barely scratch the surface</li>
          <li>Written by people who clearly haven't used the tools</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>I wanted something different. Real usage. Real opinions. No fluff.</p>
        
        <h2>My Testing Methodology</h2>
        
        <p>Every tool I review goes through a structured testing process:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Minimum 2 weeks of real usage</strong> - Not playing with demos, actual production work</li>
          <li><strong>Same prompts across competitors</strong> - Fair, head-to-head comparisons</li>
          <li><strong>Time tracking</strong> - Measuring actual productivity impact</li>
          <li><strong>Quality scoring</strong> - Rating outputs against specific criteria</li>
          <li><strong>Long-term follow-up</strong> - Checking if initial impressions hold</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>I pay for my own subscriptions. No free access in exchange for positive reviews. My opinions are my own, and I'll tell you when something sucks just as quickly as I'll tell you when something genuinely impresses me.</p>
        
        <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>In-depth comparisons</strong> - Side-by-side tests with real examples</li>
          <li><strong>Honest pros and cons</strong> - No tool is perfect, and I won't pretend otherwise</li>
          <li><strong>Practical tutorials</strong> - How to actually use these tools, not just what they do</li>
          <li><strong>Updated recommendations</strong> - AI tools change fast; I try to keep up</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>The Name</h2>
        
        <p>GenAIPick comes from "GenAI Pick" - as in, your go-to source for picking the right Generative AI tools. Simple enough.</p>
        
        <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
        
        <p>Have a tool you want me to review? Found something outdated? Just want to say hi? <a href="/contact/">Drop me a message</a>.</p>
        
        <p>Thanks for being here.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
